social_posts.post_text:
You asked for it! The Lobster Roll painting is finally here!! 🦞🥖☀️ This painting was inspired by an awesome photo from @themainefoodies and I think it perfectly captures a New England summer memory! Prints will be up on my site very very soon!

The original will be on display at @bostonpublicmarket and is available for sale. It’s 24x30, $450. DM to purchase.
Have you visited me at @bostonpublicmarket yet?! It’s where I do all of my painting and printing! If you haven’t, stop by any day. We’re open 10-6 Sunday-Tuesday and 10-7 Wednesday-Saturday!
Here’s a rare behind the scenes look at my process when I have to add a finishing touch to a composition! 😘🤌🏻🍷This was all done in my little studio at @bostonpublicmarket!

This corner of my @bostonpublicmarket studio/shop holds the main ingredient for my paintings: @goldenpaints!! No other brand has the vibrancy and texture  that they do!

Come visit me Monday-Thursdays and visit my awesome employees on the weekends! 10-6 Sun-Tues; 10-7 Wed-Sat
No place I’d rather be than @bostonpublicmarket on a rainy day! Come visit me until 6 today!

My latest New England series is now available as prints!! Check out the four new designs at laurelgreenfieldart.com/prints and in the link in my bio! 

These paintings were a collaboration with @themainefoodies and @ecefeasts and I can’t wait to share the stories behind the photos with you!

You can also shop in person at @bostonpublicmarket
Watching people interact with my art makes me so happy I could cry 😭🥰. Come visit me at @bostonpublicmarket every day!

Currently I’m in a season of painting! 🎨 sometimes when I have too many events I don’t get to paint a lot but in the first few months of the year, it’s typically quiet enough to get through some bigger pieces. If you want to watch me work on these, I typically paint on Monday, Wednesday, and Thursdays at @bostonpublicmarket!

And if you want to take a class with me, the next Paint and Sip is at BPM next Thursday March 30 at 6:30pm! The link to sign up is in my bio! Just click on events!
I’ve been working on this piece at @bostonpublicmarket specifically for the @boswineexpo!! Prints are officially available in person at the market and will be available online very soon!
The giant oyster painting has found a forever home!! Thank you so much Molly and Jordan for sharing how special this painting is to you and for decorating your first home together with it! 🥰🦪

The Bar Cart print is one of my best selling new prints, but did you know it’s a painting of my dads actual bar cart? Swipe to see the inspiration!

And shop prints online and in person at @bostonpublicmarket!
Don’t forget to get your mom or mother figure a card for Mother’s Day! I’ve got super cute cards at @bostonpublicmarket waiting for you!
Market season is back!! ☀️ come see me at @sowaboston and @themakersshow today!!
I’m back at the Westport Fine Arts Festival this weekend! Come visit me on Elm St from 10-5 today and tomorrow!

Don’t forget to sign up for June Paint and Sip! We are painting ice cream!!! 

Tickets are $64 and include all materials and your first beverage. Grab a friend and come paint with me!
In my happy place! Come visit us at @bostonpublicmarket every day!
🎨PAINT AND SIP🍹Join me at @bostonpublicmarket for another painting workshop on June 15th! Link in my bio to sign up, just click events in the menu!
I hope your 4th of July weekend is full of ice cream and other delicious treats! 🍦I won’t be at any markets this weekend but my @bostonpublicmarket shop will be open all weekend!

Last year we started a tradition of buying a piece of original art for our anniversary instead of gifts for each other. This year we found a gorgeous painting at @goodsogunquit by artist @ricdellabernarda !

But this year is even more special because it’s our last anniversary before we become a family of 3! I can’t wait to bring Baby Botwick back to Ogunquit and share our love of food and art with him! 

Swipe to see my favorite little ultrasound pic of tiny Tater Tot! 

💓🥹
Happy Rocket Pop Day! We are open at @bostonpublicmarket today so if you have the day off and want to support some local businesses, come on down to the market!!
Finally back at @neopenmarkets this weekend! Come see Jess and me until 5!

It’s Day 1 of @americasmartatl!!!!! 🌈💥 I am SO excited to see how the show goes and so grateful that my mom and sister are here with me!

This is my very first wholesale show so I’m super proud of myself!! Hopefully we’ll start getting my art into stores around the country! 

If you’re here, I’m in building 3, floor 2, booth 515

If you’re not here, head to Faire and find me there!

Tater Tot and I are ready for Day 3! I think I underestimated how much extra energy it would take to do this pregnant 🤪. There’s a little storage space behind my booth and I may have taken a little power nap back there yesterday afternoon… But now I’m rested and ready for another day of meeting people and selling art! 

Come see me in Building 3, Floor 2, Booth 515 or shop on Faire!

I’d say my first ever wholesale show was a success! i was so nervous leading up to it because I was so anxious about whether I could do it and how it would go. Im so glad I took the risk. I couldn’t have done it without so much support from my mom and sister helping me every step of the way! I can’t wait to tell Tater Tot all about it when he gets here. Here’s our whole week condensed into a few minutes!
Welcome to Laurel Greenfield Art Headquarters at @bostonpublicmarket! We get A LOT done in a 10’x10’ space! Come see us 7 days a week between 10-6 Sun-Tu and 10-7 W-Sat
It’s FINALLY nice out in Boston today! I’m still in Wisconsin but my lovely sister @42wallabywayy set up my markets for me so you can shop all day at @sowaboston and @greenwayartisanmarket!

Brix, Brine, and ‘Gansett. I think I might keep painting this photo until I’ve exhausted every color palette!

This version is available as a print in 4 sizes on my site!
I love when my paintings find permanent homes! Thank you to this lovely couple for giving it such a gorgeous home overlooking downtown Boston!

Do you want to unleash your artistic potential? 🌟 @laurelgreenfieldart’s Hack is here to guide you. Discover how to overcome the challenge of choosing what to paint and learn how to find your unique inspiration by drawing from your life, culture, and experiences.

Discover more on the app. Link in bio.

#Arttips #inspiration #artisthack #UptimeApp #NewHack

Starting a new series! Each one is starting with an ombré background made with @goldenpaints fluid acrylics. I’m using titanium white, ultramarine blue, phthalo blue (red shade), phthalo turquoise, and quinacridone magenta!
I’m back on Newbury St today outside @motherjuice!! Come see me and get some prints! ☀️🍌🍉🍓🥤Thank you @motherjuice for supporting local artists and small businesses!!!

It’s painting season! I usually get a lot of painting done in the spring and then again in the fall and I’m so glad I’m feeling well enough to show up and paint. This fall is all about more New England memories so I can bring them to the Scituate Art Festival in Rhode Island in October!!

If you’re in @bostonpublicmarket and I’m there painting, always stop and say hi!

New Workshop Alert! 📣Sunday September 17th I’m hosting a Paint & Sundae Event at @bostonpublicmarket with ice cream from @crescentridge!

I’ll walk you through the painting process and you’ll leave with a gorgeous painting of a sundae after eating one yourself!

All ages are welcome and all materials are included. Seats are limited. 

Sign up with the link below or link in my bio!

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/paint-sundae-tickets-706319048287?aff=oddtdtcreator

Labor Day Weekend Print Sale! 📣 20% off all prints on Etsy only!

I hope your Labor Day weekend is full of fun, family, friends, food, or all of the above! 

Find the link in my story or visit Etsy.com/shop/laurelgreenfieldart

Sooo grateful to be feeling well enough at this stage of pregnancy to be able to be at markets and meet some of you in person! ☀️🤰🏻Tater Tot and I will be on Newbury Street in front of @motherjuice today! And my hero of a sister who helps me do the heavy lifting will be at @greenwayartisanmarket today!

Painting Workshop!! 🍦Come paint this sundae with me at @bostonpublicmarket and eat a sundae from @crescentridge on Sunday 9/17 at 1pm!

Get tickets with the link in my bio and at https://www.eventbrite.com/e/paint-sundae-tickets-706319048287?aff=oddtdtcreator

OCTOBER PAINTING WORKSHOP! 🦪 🦪🦪 Paint an oyster with me at @bostonpublicmarket on Wednesday October 18 at 6:30pm!

Sign up with the link in my bio or at https://www.eventbrite.com/e/paint-sip-painting-oysters-tickets-722924495627?aff=oddtdtcreator
Next Step: Outlining with Fluid Acrylics from @goldenpaints!!

My New Nostalgic Print Collection is Here!!! 🤩 It combines my childhood growing up in Atlanta - hence the Waffle House - with my adulthood spent in New England! 

I hope you love these as much as I do! 

Each in available on my website and comes in 4 sizes! They’re also available in person at @bostonpublicmarket 

Link in bio or laurelgreenfieldart.com/prints to shop!

The Oyster Painting Workshop sold out so I added another! 🦪 🎨 Thursday November 2 at @bostonpublicmarket !!

Link in bio to sign up!

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/paint-sip-painting-a-dozen-oysters-tickets-726910668377?aff=oddtdtcreator

💞THIS SUNDAY at Open Newbury Street we are welcoming @laurelgreenfieldart one more time!!💞

Have you SEEN her artwork? (Swipe➡️➡️) to check it out! 

Laurel is a longtime friend of MoJu, we adore her and you will be sure to adore her art!!✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

Stop by this Sunday, Oct 1 from 11am-4pm to say hello!!🥰

Today is my last outdoor market before holiday markets start! This season has been rainy and challenging but we made it through!

Come see us outside @motherjuice on Newbury St to shop!
For my newest paintings on paper, @frameiteasy sent me some amazing frames to make them look their best!  You can use the url frameiteasy.com/laurel for 10% off frames this whole month!

I’m back at the Scituate Art Festival in Rhode Island for the first time in two years! It’s one of the few shows I’ll travel out of Boston to. 

Come see Sydney, Tater Tot, and me through Monday!

This is my absolute favorite painting from my newest collection. Something about the purple and the teal together 😍🦪

30”x40”, acrylic on canvas, $900 plus shipping. DM to purchase
Comments are off for my and Tater Tot’s health. If you’d like to have a respectful conversation and you know me in real life, you know how to reach me.

I can’t stop painting this photo I took at @brixbrine a few years ago! I like to crop it differently and swap out the beer every time I paint it! 

Prints are now on my website!

We are in New York this weekend finishing up Tater Tot’s world tour of baby showers and family love! Then we are back to Boston to finish setting up his room AND the holiday art markets. It’s going to be an extra fun holiday season!!!

Waffle House: My Childhood Happy Place. I know it’s a fun place at 2am but when I think of @wafflehouseofficial i think of going there with my dad every Sunday morning when I was little. So you can either interpret this glowing Waffle House painting as middle of the night or break of dawn! 

Prints are available in my shop AND you can see the original painting in its forever home if you swipe! 🧇💕

NEW PRINTS ARE HERE! 🤪 We’ve got the much-anticipated SpongeBob popsicle, the hot sauce print, chocolate chips, and a pretzel!

All are available at laurelgreenfieldart.com/prints
I cannot believe it’s already Snowport season. And I really cannot believe I’ll have a baby before it’s over 🤪🥰🥹🤗😵‍💫 Come shop at Snowport every day from now til the end of the year!!!

Introducing larger canvas prints! Right now I have select designs available for purchase at Snowport @themakersshow including this bar cart! Swipe to see more canvas prints! 

The larger ones are 24”x30” and are $250. If you’d like to order another design as a canvas print just DM me!

It’s Snowport season again! I have an amazing team who are ready to help you pick out the perfect art for yourself or as gifts! Come see us every day between now and the end of the year in @seaportbos at @themakersshow !!

“Omg They’re Bagels!” is what we hear over and over again at markets and I love it! 🥯🌻 This print is available in all sizes both in person at @bostonpublicmarket and @seaportbos @themakersshow! Come shop every day!

I love seeing the print combos you come up with! What a sweet set! 

You can get these designs online and in person at @seaportbos @themakersshow and @bostonpublicmarket every day!

Raise your hand if you want a fancy margarita! ✋🏻 This painting started as a commission but it’s become so loved that it’s now one of my best selling prints. 

It’s available in every size in person and online AND we have it in 24”x30” canvas prints at Snowport! Come shop every day.

Everything about this year’s Snowport booth makes me so happy! It really feels like a reflection of who I’ve become as an artist as well as what I’ve always been inspired by! Come visit every day until the end of the year!

Ornaments are back!!!! This year we have Dunkin, Butter, and Bagels!!!

Right now they are available in person at Snowport @themakersshow and @seaportbos and @bostonpublicmarket 

They’ll be online very soon!!!

Happy Tuesday! Today is the perfect day to come down to Snowport from 3-8 and shop! Come grab this print inspired by @bubblebathboston and @tenderonisboston at @highstreetplace!!! I have it in 3 sizes for you! 

AND mark your calendar for opening day at @sowaboston Winter Festival this Friday! 

Bonus Shopping Tip… As always you can skip all the long holiday market lines and get this print at @bostonpublicmarket at my shop there!!!

Introducing my greatest masterpiece ever… JESSE! 🥹🐣🥔 He decided to come 2 and a half weeks early and join the party! We had a super long labor and a brief stay in the NICU but luckily he is doing so great and hopefully we will all be going home soon!

I can’t wait for him to meet some of you at markets and for him to experience life with an artist mom!

Took us all week to finally get a photo of the 3 of us! Our first family photo! 🥰 This week was so emotional and I still can’t believe how fast it went, how slow it went, and how much I still need to process. I have a million fears about how the heck to be a mom to this beautiful little peanut and how the heck to run my business while being a great mom. I’m glad I have other artist moms to show me the way. 🥹

After a brief moment of panic about a protest targeting one of my holiday markets and a viral text spreading a rumor about something really bad happening at the market, I’ve come to my senses and put the menorah back out after telling my employees to put it away. 

We can’t just hide. It is 2023 not 1943. My business is proudly Jewish-owned and as scary as it is, being proud is the best thing I can do right now. 

Happy second night of Chanukah!

This right here is the highlight of my year as an artist! Getting to bring my son to snowport with @jeff.botwick even for 15 minutes just to deliver bags is the cherry on top of a year that was spent planning everything around him! He’s my new reason for creating, sharing, and selling art and n can’t wait for him to grow up and see everything I do! And for him to hopefully paint with me!
Jesse would like to wish you all a Merry Christmas! 🎁🎄 Stay tuned for more digital drawings! Playing on my iPad feels a little easier for me these days than painting but I’ll get back to it soon!
null

It’s January 18th at @bostonpublicmarket! Sign up now under the events tab on my website! Laurelgreenfieldart.com/events
